    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*haϑya-ka,</w></mentioned>,
        ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>haṭhṭhā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из
                %ihaϑya%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from
                    %ihaϑya%i)</note><gloss><q>правда</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>haiϑya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>satyá-</w><gloss><q>истинный</q></gloss></mentioned>; %iti%i дало %iс%i,
        как обычно (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_acc"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arc"/> и
        др.); начальное %ih%i отпало, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æd"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmæ"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_avd"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_aǧd"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærzæ"/>. Краткая форма слова (без
        суффиксального %i-æg%i) сохранилась в выражении <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æccæj"/>?
        „правда ли?“, а также в %iæv-æʒ-a%i, %iæv-æʒ-i%i ‘по правде’, ‘вероятно’. Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æcc-"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæʒa"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ævæʒi"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæccægæn"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æcægælon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19,
                168, 207, 214</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*haϑya-ka,</w></mentioned>,
        cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>haṭhṭhā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из
                %ihaϑya%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from
                    %ihaϑya%i)</note><gloss><q>truth</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>haiϑya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>satyá-</w><gloss><q>true</q></gloss></mentioned>; %iti%i gave %iс%i, as
        usually (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_acc"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arc"/>
        etc.); the initial %ih%i disappeared, as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æd"/>, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_æmæ"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_avd"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_aǧd"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærzæ"/>. Short form of the word
        (without suffix %i-æg%i) was preserved in the expression <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æccæj"/>? “is it true?” as well as in %iæv-æʒ-a%i, %iæv-æʒ-i%i ‘to tell
        the truth’, ‘probably’. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æcc-"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ævæʒa"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæʒi"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ævæccægæn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æcægælon"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19, 168, 207, 214</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
